<div><h1 id=3D"computational-graph-introduction">Computational Graph Introd=
uction</h1>
<h2 id=3D"what-is-a-computational-graph">What is a computational graph ?</h=
2>
<p>A computational graph is a directed graph that represents the computatio=
n of a mathematical function. It is a graph of nodes and edges, where each =
node represents a mathematical operation and each edge represents the flow =
of data between the operations.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Why use a computational graph ?</strong>
A computational graph is used to represent the computation of a mathematica=
l function. It is a graph of nodes and edges, where each node represents a =
mathematical operation and each edge represents the flow of data between th=
e operations.</p>
